454
00:41:09,400 --> 00:41:15,320
didn't hear back. On the third morning he 
figured something was up, so he fired up Gmail,  

455
00:41:15,320 --> 00:41:22,280
went to his sent mail, and you guessed it, there 
were no sent mails there. So something had broken  

456
00:41:22,280 --> 00:41:27,600
with mailbox. So he's cursing to himself trying 
to remind himself everything's going to be  

457
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:36,960
okay. Sent all the same emails from 
Gmail manually and they all came through. 

458
00:41:36,960 --> 00:41:41,680
But then one of the investors said, "Hey, by the 
way, you might want to check your email clients,  

459
00:41:41,680 --> 00:41:46,880
because I've been getting some of your emails 
twice." Now he goes back into his Gmail, he sees  

460
00:41:46,880 --> 00:41:52,280
that yes, actually the original emails that were 
queued up in mailbox have now indeed been sent,  

461
00:41:52,280 --> 00:41:56,800
and some of the investors, and unfortunately most 
