469
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:40,600
mission-critical. It's not something where you 
can simply launch with a half-baked product.

470
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:43,600
This is such an important nuance 
take on, there's always this debate,  

471
00:42:43,600 --> 00:42:48,920
how much to focus on craft and user experience, 
how much to focus on time to launch and get it  

472
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:53,480
out and speed. What I'm hearing here, which 
I completely agree with is, it depends on the  

473
00:42:53,480 --> 00:42:59,440
market you're in and the criticality essentially 
of your product. So if it's email, it just needs  

474
00:42:59,440 --> 00:43:03,200
to work and you need to get that right, you need 
to spend all the time, you need to get that right. 

475
00:43:03,200 --> 00:43:06,400
This reminds me of something else that 
when your early investors shared with me,  

476
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:10,800
Bill Trenchard from First-Round Capital. He 
